author: Source: WSYR-AM Syracuse
title: Seahawks Send Lions To 0-And-4 Start - WSYR-AM Syracuse
text:
Kam Chancellor stripped Calvin Johnson at the goal line with less than two minutes to play as the Seahawks pulled out a 13-10 win over the Lions on "Monday Night Football" at CenturyLink Field. K.J. Wright knocked the ball through the back of the end zone for a touchback on the play, sending Detroit to its first 0-and-4 start since 2010.
 WSYR-AM Syracuse.
